### Tutorial #1 for Player Movement

 Before you start with the code you want to make sure you select 



This is the code for the player movement, this code allows te player to move in different directions it also includes a speed limit that you can set when playing the game.
  
       `Input.GetAxis("Horizontal")`
     This input corresponds to the movement of the player moving left/right 

        Input.GetAxis("Vertical")
      This input corresponds to the movement of the player moving up/down 

`float horizontalInput = Input.GetAxis("Horizontal");
        float verticalInput = Input.GetAxis("Vertical");`

        rb.velocity = new Vector3(horizontalInput * movementSpeed, rb.velocity.y, verticalInput * movementSpeed);`


